<p><a name="External_links" id="External_links"></a></p>
<h2><span class="editsection">[<a href="/w/index.php?title=Ray_tracing_(graphics)&amp;action=edit&amp;section=15" title="Edit section: External links">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline">External links</span></h2>
<ul>
<li><a href="http://www.scratchapixel.com/tutorials/home/home.php" class="external text" title="http://www.scratchapixel.com/tutorials/home/home.php" rel="nofollow">Ray-tracing and 3D rendering tutorials</a> - free tutorials on ray-tracing and rendering techniques with source code</li>
<li><a href="http://www.codermind.com/articles/Raytracer-in-C++-Introduction-What-is-ray-tracing.html" class="external text" title="http://www.codermind.com/articles/Raytracer-in-C++-Introduction-What-is-ray-tracing.html" rel="nofollow">What is ray tracing&#160;?</a> - An ongoing tutorial of ray tracing in several parts from basic to more advanced topics</li>
<li><a href="http://www.pcper.com/article.php?aid=506" class="external text" title="http://www.pcper.com/article.php?aid=506" rel="nofollow">Ray tracing and Gaming - One Year Later</a> - Daniel Pohl's follow up on the benefits of ray tracing over rasterization for games</li>
<li><a href="http://www.raytracingnews.org/" class="external text" title="http://www.raytracingnews.org/" rel="nofollow">The Ray Tracing News</a> – short research articles and new links to resources</li>
<li><a href="http://www.few.vu.nl/~kielmann/theses/avdploeg.pdf" class="external text" title="http://www.few.vu.nl/~kielmann/theses/avdploeg.pdf" rel="nofollow">Interactive Ray Tracing: The replacement of rasterization?</a> – thesis about real time ray tracing and its state in December 2006</li>
<li><a href="http://graphics.cs.uni-sb.de/RTGames/" class="external text" title="http://graphics.cs.uni-sb.de/RTGames/" rel="nofollow">Games using realtime raytracing</a></li>
<li><a href="http://www.nirenstein.com/e107/page.php?11" class="external text" title="http://www.nirenstein.com/e107/page.php?11" rel="nofollow">SSRT</a> – C++ source code for a Monte-carlo ray/pathtracer (supporting GI) - written with ease of understanding in mind.</li>
<li><a href="http://www.devmaster.net/articles/raytracing_series/part1.php" class="external text" title="http://www.devmaster.net/articles/raytracing_series/part1.php" rel="nofollow">A series of tutorials on implementing a raytracer using C++</a></li>
<li><a href="http://irtc.org/" class="external text" title="http://irtc.org/" rel="nofollow">The Internet Ray Tracing Competition</a> – still and animated categories</li>
<li><a href="http://www.pcper.com/article.php?aid=334" class="external text" title="http://www.pcper.com/article.php?aid=334" rel="nofollow">Quake 4 Raytraced by Daniel Pohl</a> – good information on potential for real-time ray traced games</li>
<li><a href="http://www.barakcohen.co.il/2008/10/ray-tracing-simple-java-open-source.html" class="external text" title="http://www.barakcohen.co.il/2008/10/ray-tracing-simple-java-open-source.html" rel="nofollow">Ray Tracing: A Simple Java, Open Source Implementation</a> - Simple open-sourced Java implementation aimed at Computer Science students.</li>
<li><a href="http://wiioperasdk.com/raytrace/raytrace.html" class="external text" title="http://wiioperasdk.com/raytrace/raytrace.html" rel="nofollow">JavaScript Ray Tracer</a> - A simple and highly-optimized ray tracer that draws to a canvas (will not work in Internet Explorer)</li>
<li><a href="http://www.caustic.com/" class="external text" title="http://www.caustic.com/" rel="nofollow">CausticRT</a> first real time ray tracing platform</li>
</ul>
